From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 11:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX Route B rd_native taa_resolve
 in-frame resolve replacement

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040 + 0041 (the branch-HEAD gpu_culling tail plus the
tonemap and ssao_blur rd_native slices). This is the third Route B REAL
replacement pass: Route B drives the Rurix taa_resolve kernel as a first-class
in-frame RenderingDevice compute dispatch, replacing ONLY the native resolve()
compute dispatch inside TAA::process while the native history-maintenance copies
(temp->internal, internal->history, velocity->prev_velocity) still run, so the
temporal feedback loop is preserved. When it records, the native Godot resolve
dispatch is genuinely skipped (no scaffold clear, unlike patch 0019).

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_taa_resolve_rd_native(RID color, RID depth, RID velocity,
  RID prev_velocity, RID history, RID output_temp, Size2i internal_size,
  float disocclusion_threshold, float variance_dynamic). It takes the six Godot
  RID handles in the container's binding order (color/depth/velocity/
  prev_velocity/history = SRV t0..t4, output temp = UAV u0) instead of the native
  ID3D12Resource* handles the shim-path try_record_taa_resolve takes, so the
  module can build an RD uniform set and compute pipeline directly. Base returns
  false, so hooks that do not override it keep the native path.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings,
  independent of the four existing taa_resolve shim settings (untouched):
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/backend (int, default 0;
  0=disabled / 1=shim / 2=rd_native) and
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/rd_container_path (string, default "").
  Defaults keep the RD-native path disabled.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_taa_resolve_rd_native
  override. Lazily builds the compute pipeline once (FileAccess reads the Rurix
  container -> shader_create_from_bytecode -> compute_pipeline_create, latching
  rd_native_taa_resolve_load_failed on any failure so it is not retried per
  frame), runs a usage-bits preflight (five SRV inputs SAMPLING_BIT, temp output
  STORAGE_BIT), binds the six resolve resources via UniformSetCacheRD, packs the
  28-byte b0 push constants ([i64 resolution_width, i64 resolution_height,
  f32 disocclusion_threshold, f32 variance_dynamic, f32 reserved0]), and
  dispatches ceil(size/8) groups with its own compute_list_begin/end (resolve()
  is a standalone list, unlike the shared SSAO list). No submit()/sync() (a
  local-RD-only concept). The one-shot RXGD_RD_NATIVE_TAA_RESOLVE active marker
  is emitted via print_verbose when the pipeline is first built (not per-frame).
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/effects/taa.cpp: in TAA::process's !just_allocated
  branch, backend == 2 runs the rd_native gate in place of resolve(); a successful
  record skips the native resolve dispatch, and the three history-maintenance
  copies below still run so the feedback loop is preserved. backend != 2 leaves
  the pre-existing resolve()+copies chain byte-for-byte unchanged. Adds
  core/config/project_settings.h + drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h includes.

Fail-closed everywhere: with the default backend == 0 (and empty container path),
rd_native is never engaged and the native Godot TAA resolve renders. The rd_native
path replaces only the resolve compute dispatch and preserves the native history
copies, so the TAA feedback loop is intact; TAA is temporal, so multi-frame
convergence evidence is required to characterize the replacement. RXGD_ABI_VERSION
is unchanged (this path does not touch the C ABI struct layout and sets no
RxGdCaps.flags bit; rd_native is bridge-independent). No performance claim is made.
